&lt;p&gt;[original]:&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="Korean.Recipes" /><category term="Fast.Easy.Recipes" /><summary type="html">You’ll find this post in your _posts directory. Go ahead and edit it and re-build the site to see your changes. You can rebuild the site in many different ways, but the most common way is to run jekyll serve, which launches a web server and auto-regenerates your site when a file is updated.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Stroller Review: UPPAbaby Vista VS Minu</title><link href="/product.reviews/2021/01/19/vistaminu.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Stroller Review: UPPAbaby Vista VS Minu" /><published>2021-01-19T17:38:57-08:00</published><updated>2021-01-19T17:38:57-08:00</updated><id>/product.reviews/2021/01/19/vistaminu</id><content type="html" xml:base="/product.reviews/2021/01/19/vistaminu.html">&lt;p&gt;When we first set out to buy a stroller for our first baby, we couldn not find too many firsthand comparison reviews between the Uppababy Vista and UPPAbaby Minu. We first bought the Vista, then the Minu, and have some experience using the two and have opinions on which we would recommend to new parents, so here is a video summarizing our thoughts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&quot;716&quot; height=&quot;402&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/96IzT05njq8&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Overall, I think if we were to go back in time and pick only one stroller we would choose the Minu. We like the stroller more because it has a smaller foot print and it much more portable. The weight is a plus when traveling, but it is also a big plus for everyday use.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;UPPAbaby Vista (969.99): &lt;a href=&quot;https://uppababy.com/vista/&quot;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;UPPAbaby Minu ($399.99): &lt;a href=&quot;https://uppababy.com/minu/&quot;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Minu Car Seat Adapters ($24.99): &lt;a href=&quot;https://uppababy.com/product/minu-adapters-mesa/&quot;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Minu Travel Bag ($89.99): &lt;a href=&quot;https://uppababy.com/product/minu-travel-bag/&quot;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="Product.Reviews" /><summary type="html">When we first set out to buy a stroller for our first baby, we couldn not find too many firsthand comparison reviews between the Uppababy Vista and UPPAbaby Minu. We first bought the Vista, then the Minu, and have some experience using the two and have opinions on which we would recommend to new parents, so here is a video summarizing our thoughts.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Korean Style Short Ribs LA Galbi (갈비) Recipe</title><link href="/korean.recipes/fast.easy.recipes/2021/01/11/lagalbi.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Korean Style Short Ribs LA Galbi (갈비) Recipe" /><published>2021-01-11T17:38:57-08:00</published><updated>2021-01-11T17:38:57-08:00</updated><id>/korean.recipes/fast.easy.recipes/2021/01/11/lagalbi</id><content type="html" xml:base="/korean.recipes/fast.easy.recipes/2021/01/11/lagalbi.html">&lt;p&gt;LA Galbi is probably the most well known Korean dish outside of Korea. It is a
sweet soy sauce marinade that even the most pickiest people will enjoy. There are
many recipes but the marinade mainly consists of sugar, soy sauce, garlic and
onion. The Korean pear is often added because the enyzmes help tenderize the
meat making it easier to chew! In our recipe we use less soy sauce and sugar,
but feel free to adjust the ratios to your and your family’s liking!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&quot;716&quot; height=&quot;402&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/I9yG82MDbu4&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Original Recipe: &lt;a href=&quot;https://mykoreankitchen.com/la-galbi/&quot;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Ingredients&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;~&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;lbs&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;beef&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;short&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;ribs&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;cut&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;into&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;strips&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;easily&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;found&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Asian&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;groceries&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Marinade&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sweet&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;onion&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Korean&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;pear&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;or&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Fuji&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;apple&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;cloves&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;garlic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;peeled&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;inch&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;piece&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;ginger&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;cup&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;firmly&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;packed&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;dark&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;brown&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sugar&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;cup&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;soy&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sauce&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;cup&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;water&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;tablespoons&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;dark&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sesame&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Directions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Soak&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;meat&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;water&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;hour&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;optional&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Mince&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;onion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;pear&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;garlic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;ginger&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;add&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sugar&lt;/span&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;soy&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;sauce&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;water&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Place&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;meat&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;marinade&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;fridge&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;24&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;hours&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;Grill&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;meat&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;stove&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;oven&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;or&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;grill!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="Korean.Recipes" /><category term="Fast.Easy.Recipes" /><summary type="html">LA Galbi is probably the most well known Korean dish outside of Korea. It is a sweet soy sauce marinade that even the most pickiest people will enjoy. There are many recipes but the marinade mainly consists of sugar, soy sauce, garlic and onion. The Korean pear is often added because the enyzmes help tenderize the meat making it easier to chew! In our recipe we use less soy sauce and sugar, but feel free to adjust the ratios to your and your family’s liking!</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Bolognese</title><link href="/2021/01/07/bolognese.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Bolognese" /><published>2021-01-07T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2021-01-07T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>/2021/01/07/bolognese</id><content type="html" xml:base="/2021/01/07/bolognese.html"></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Korean Style Pancake (부추부침개) Recipe</title><link href="/korean.recipes/fast.easy.recipes/2021/01/05/koreanpancake.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Korean Style Pancake (부추부침개) Recipe" /><published>2021-01-05T17:38:57-08:00</published><updated>2021-01-05T17:38:57-08:00</updated><id>/korean.recipes/fast.easy.recipes/2021/01/05/koreanpancake</id><content type="html" xml:base="/korean.recipes/fast.easy.recipes/2021/01/05/koreanpancake.html">&lt;p&gt;Korean pork ribs are usually marinaded in a spicy sauce. We tried a non-spicy version
and our toddler loved it! We were actually very surprised at how much he enjoyed
chewing the meat off the ribs. This recipe takes a couple hours. Baking the
ribs for a long time at a low heat makes the meat much more tender. The meat
just falls off the bone! We use less sugar and soy sauce the the original recipe
but the ribs were still very delicious!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;iframe width=&quot;716&quot; height=&quot;402&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/M2hezBildN8&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture&quot; allowfullscreen=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

